                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270111-110-victim1096 t18270111-110-viclabel613"></join>. On the 8th of January I lived at Mr. Burrows', at the sign of the <placeName id="t18270111-110-crimeloc614">Strong Man, public-house, Lower East Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270111-110-crimeloc614" type="placeName" value="Strong Man, public-house, Lower East Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270111-110-crimeloc614" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270111-110-off611 t18270111-110-crimeloc614"></join>. I had put two shillings, and four sixpences into a drawer in my room; it was not locked; one of the sixpences was an old coin, which I had had six months, and can swear to - the prisoner had lodged at the house ten nights, and slept on the third floor; I missed my money, and mentioned it in his presence; he said he had not been in my room; the officer was sent for, and searched him; I was called in, and saw the two shillings and four sixpences on the table; one was the old coin sixpence.</p>
